{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Server*. Using *JIRA Software Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWCLOUD-5261].
  {panel}

- When trying to choose from one of the Boards we have setup, Greenhopper doesn't bring up any Board other than Default.

- Have to manually enter the following code (using cntrl-shift-j) - as an example when I want to bring up our Epics Board, I have to enter the following code each time I wish display it: Boards.setCtx('Epics@!@rick').

*Steps to reproduce*
# Go to {{Agile >> Planning Board}}
# Create two new Contexts named 'Test1' and 'Test2'
# Try to select between the Contexts and it always go back to the default Context

{panel:title=Atlassian Status as at May 31 2012| borderStyle=solid| borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#49BD5F| bgColor=#E7F4FA}
This has been fixed in 5.10.1, please upgrade
{panel}

We intend on fixing this problem imminently. An immediate workaround that may work for some affected users in Chrome is to bring up the Console with Ctrl-Shift-J (or Cmd-Opt-J on Mac) and enter: 

   Boards.setCtx('x')

Replace the x with the name of the context
